                    <msItem n="2" xml:id="Wellcome_Ethiopian_5_2">
                        <locus from="30" to="59">Lines 30-59</locus>
                        <author key="">Anonymous</author>
                        <title key="" type="desc">Prayer against enemies, buda, barya, Legewon and magical action.</title>
                        
                        <incipit><locus>Line 30</locus>: <!-- Ge'ez text to be picked up in late-stage editing-->
                        </incipit>                      
                        
                        <note>According to Strelcyn, buda is a being with the evil eye who possesses victims by drinking their blood and eating their flesh. Barya are a people believed to serve the demon or spirit provoking epilepsy 
                            and therefore barya is identified with this disease. Legewon is a name for Satan, chief of the barya and one of the most frequently occurring devils in Ethiopic magical literature (<ref>Strelcyn</ref>)</note> 
                    </msItem>
                    
